        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 18 at 6:22PM EDT until July 18 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 622 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Jetersville, or
8 miles west of Amelia Courthouse, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind damage to
trees and powerlines.

Locations impacted include...
Amelia Courthouse, Chula, Jetersville, Morven, Scotts Fork,
Paineville, Maplewood, Deatonville, Rodophil, Truxillo, Winterham,
and Denaro.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
